  "prompt": "How do I prepare SBI PO?",
  "response": "To prepare for the SBI PO (Probationary Officer) exam, follow these steps:\n\n1. Understand the Exam Pattern\n- Prelims: Objective type\n- Mains: Descriptive and objective type\n- Interview\n\n2. Study Materials\n- Standard books for banking exams\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Online mock tests\n- Current affairs magazines\n\n3. Subject-wise Preparation\na) Quantitative Aptitude\n- Practice math problems\n- Learn shortcut techniques\n- Focus on speed and accuracy\n\nb) Reasoning\n- Practice logical reasoning\n- Solve puzzles and data interpretation\n- Mock tests for time management\n\nc) English Language\n- Improve grammar\n- Reading comprehension\n- Vocabulary\n- Practice writing skills\n\nd) Computer Knowledge\n- Basic computer fundamentals\n- Microsoft Office\n- Internet basics\n\ne) General Awareness\n- Current affairs\n- Banking awareness\n- Economy and finance\n- National and international news\n\n4. Preparation Strategy\n- Create a study schedule\n- Consistent practice\n- Take online mock tests\n- Analyze your performance\n- Work on weak areas\n\n5. Additional Tips\n- Stay updated with banking news\n- Maintain physical and mental fitness\n- Time management\n- Solve previous years' papers\n\nBest of luck with your preparation!",
